The `UserBaseDto` has `@IsEmail() @IsNotEmpty() email: string` — an empty string or null email would fail validation. When `userModel.create` is called with an empty email, it validates first: `validate(dto, { skipMissingProperties: true })`. With `skipMissingProperties: true`, an empty string would still fail `@IsNotEmpty()` and `@IsEmail()`.

So I can't pass an empty email to create a user. The auth.service code at line 173-178:
```typescript
const newUser = await this.userService.create({
    data: {
        email: profile.email,     // empty string
        name: profile.name,
        avatar_url: profile.avatar_url,
    },
});
```

This would fail because `email: ''` fails `@IsEmail()` and `@IsNotEmpty()` validation.

I need a different approach. Let me look at `IUserCreate` to see if email can be null/optional:

